🛠️ Task 1 – Create Branches

List branches

git branch

Create branch

git branch feature-login

Switch

git checkout feature-login

Or

git switch feature-login

Create & switch

git checkout -b feature-dashboard
🛠️ Task 2 – Merge Branch

Switch to main

git checkout main

Merge

git merge feature-dashboard

Delete merged branch

git branch -d feature-dashboard
🛠️ Task 3 – Merge Conflict

Edit the same line in two branches.

Merge:

git merge feature-login

Conflict example:

<<<<<<< HEAD
Production Code
=======
Development Code
>>>>>>> feature-login

Resolve manually, then:

git add .

git commit
🛠️ Task 4 – Git Rebase

Move commits on top of another branch

git checkout feature-api

git rebase main

Abort

git rebase --abort

Continue

git rebase --continue
🛠️ Task 5 – Git Stash

Save changes temporarily

git stash

List

git stash list

Restore

git stash pop
🛠️ Task 6 – Git Tags

Create lightweight tag

git tag v1.0

Annotated tag

git tag -a v1.0 -m "First Release"

List tags

git tag

Push tags

git push origin --tags
🛠️ Task 7 – Remote Repository

Show remote

git remote -v

Add remote

git remote add origin https://github.com/username/project.git

Push

git push -u origin main
🛠️ Task 8 – Fetch vs Pull

Fetch

git fetch

Pull

git pull

Difference:

git fetch downloads changes but does not merge them.
git pull downloads and merges changes.
🛠️ Task 9 – Reset & Revert

Soft reset

git reset --soft HEAD~1

Hard reset (⚠️ destructive)

git reset --hard HEAD~1

Safe revert

git revert HEAD
🛠️ Task 10 – Cherry-pick

Copy one commit

git cherry-pick <commit-hash>

Useful for moving a single bug fix to another branch.

